1
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:11,625
[bubbling lava]

2
00:00:11,708 --> 00:00:15,375
[footsteps]

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,708
So the smelting
is already completed.

4
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:32,958
[grunts]

5
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:43,375
Loading, loading,
loading, loading.

6
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:47,666
All systems online,
Murakumo activating.

7
00:00:49,958 --> 00:00:51,333
[NU] Ragna!

8
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:55,458
[NU] Come here to
kill me again, silly?

9
00:00:55,541 --> 00:00:59,250
[RAGNA] Killing's for
people. You get broken.

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,750
Oh, Ragna I love it
when you talk dirty.

11
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:05,250
Come here. Let's play.

12
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:16,416
[laughs playfully]

13
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:17,875
[RAGNA] Dammit!

14
00:01:32,166 --> 00:01:33,166
[laughs playfully]

15
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:35,000
Ahhh!

16
00:01:37,541 --> 00:01:38,666
Son of a--!

17
00:01:39,791 --> 00:01:41,791
[stabbing]
[RAGNA cries out]

18
00:01:44,583 --> 00:01:46,125
You're insane.

19
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:47,458
[NU laughs playfully]

20
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:49,333
Oh, Ragna!

21
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:52,541
Now we'll be
together. Always.

22
00:01:58,333 --> 00:01:59,458
[HAZAMA] How many
times are you gonna

23
00:01:59,541 --> 00:02:02,125
let that girl shish
kabob ya, Ragna?

24
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:16,666
[RACHEL] It's always the same.

25
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:21,000
We've run the scene to death,
and again, the curtain falls.

26
00:02:21,083 --> 00:02:23,250
Sleep well,
Ragna the Bloodedge.

27
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:25,958
Our pantomime will continue.

28
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:03,708
[MALE NOL 1A] This is the
N.O.L. Ahkitsu Branch!

29
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:04,750
We're under attack!

30
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:05,916
It's the Grim Reaper!

31
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,416
He hit us out of nowhere!

32
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,958
We've taken heavy casualties!
If we don't get backup--

33
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,500
[blast]

34
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:21,541
♪

35
00:04:24,791 --> 00:04:26,416
[sighs]

36
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,541
There's plenty of
seithr down here,

37
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,500
that's for damn sure.

38
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,125
[RAGNA] Dammit!

39
00:04:47,916 --> 00:04:50,708
Underfoot again. Like dirt.

40
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,958
But dirt, I'm sure,
has better manners.

41
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:55,375
[RAGNA] Shut it!

42
00:04:58,666 --> 00:04:59,625
[GII cries out]

43
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:02,583
[GII cries out]

44
00:05:02,666 --> 00:05:04,083
My!

45
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:06,583
What the hell? Why're
you griefing me, Rabbit?

46
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:10,166
Don't be mean, Princess.
I'm a bat, not a baseball!

47
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:12,458
[RACHEL]
Your self-control is laudable.

48
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:13,875
Brute that you are,
I feared you might

49
00:05:13,958 --> 00:05:16,458
have fallen prey
to that arm of yours.

50
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:18,541
Imagine my surprise.

51
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:21,375
I'm impressed.
You're a good boy, Ragna.

52
00:05:21,458 --> 00:05:23,500
[RAGNA] Hey! I'm not
some mutt, y'know!

53
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,708
Kagutsuchi awaits you.

54
00:05:26,791 --> 00:05:27,916
Huh?

55
00:05:29,375 --> 00:05:30,791
Kagutsuchi?

56
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:34,125
Why the hell would I waste
my time with a place like that?

57
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:38,375
Course, the town's got a
Cauldron I need to destroy.

58
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,791
Hm?

59
00:05:44,875 --> 00:05:46,625
Guess I'll give it a look.

60
00:05:58,041 --> 00:06:01,666
Well if it ain't Little
Miss Blood Breath.

61
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:06,750
You spend your time
eavesdropping on a lady?

62
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:09,416
[HAZAMA] Uh huh.
When it comes to time,

63
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,666
I have got a crap ton.
I'm not gonna lie,

64
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,250
all this repeating
makes planning

65
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:16,041
ahead a real pain in the ass.

66
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:19,166
You would be wise
to do naught but watch.

67
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:21,166
Yeah, I bet
you're right, huh.

68
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:22,375
Unfortunately...

69
00:06:22,458 --> 00:06:23,750
I have way too
many irons in

70
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:26,875
the ol' fire to
call it a day now!

71
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:30,166
[laughs]

72
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:44,666
♪

73
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:45,666
[knock]

74
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:46,708
[NOEL] Excuse me, sir.

75
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:48,875
Second Lieutenant
Noel Vermillion.

76
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:52,125
[JIN] Come in.

77
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:59,166
Major Kisaragi,
I bring this.

78
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:12,791
[JIN] The dispatch
bears an ars magus seal.

79
00:07:12,875 --> 00:07:14,833
It's classified.

80
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:28,458
[JIN] It's him.

81
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,083
[gasps]

82
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:33,083
Finally,
Ragna the Bloodedge.

83
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:41,708
[JIN laughs]

84
00:07:41,791 --> 00:07:44,416
Major, sir. What is it?

85
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,666
Thirteenth, huh?

86
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:55,625
Move.

87
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:01,083
[door slams]

88
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:16,125
[people chattering]

89
00:08:16,208 --> 00:08:18,000
A lotta people here.

90
00:08:26,708 --> 00:08:28,083
Huh?

91
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:31,583
[groans]

92
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:36,708
[RAGNA grunts]

93
00:08:36,791 --> 00:08:39,250
[TAOKAKA] Om noms.

94
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:42,458
Tao needs om noms!

95
00:08:42,541 --> 00:08:45,083
Taokaka Punch!

96
00:08:46,791 --> 00:08:48,083
[yells]

97
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:49,750
[TAOKAKA] Meow-ch!

98
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:54,125
[TAOKAKA] Me... ow...

99
00:08:54,208 --> 00:08:57,541
Of course. Kaka Clan.

100
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:58,833
Huh?

101
00:08:58,916 --> 00:09:01,958
You don't have to
beat Tao up, mister.

102
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:05,333
[TAOKAKA] Just let her
waste away to nothin'.

103
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,541
[TAOKAKA]
Thanks for all the food!

104
00:09:07,625 --> 00:09:10,916
[eating sounds]

105
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,625
You're a good guy,
treating Tao

106
00:09:12,708 --> 00:09:14,208
to all these tasty things!

107
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:16,833
I totally got
hustled, didn't I?

108
00:09:16,916 --> 00:09:19,583
[TAOKAKA] Nope! You
Tao-tally got hustled!

109
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:20,833
Oh, by the
way Good Guy,

110
00:09:20,916 --> 00:09:22,333
do you know
where Rawrgna the

111
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:24,458
Something, Something
likes to hang out?

112
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:25,708
Huh?

113
00:09:25,791 --> 00:09:26,791
I think you're talking ab--

114
00:09:26,875 --> 00:09:28,458
[TAOKAKA] If Tao
uses her best mew-ves

115
00:09:28,541 --> 00:09:31,041
on Rawrgna and catches him,
she'll get a bunch of money!

116
00:09:31,125 --> 00:09:33,583
More than anyone ever!

117
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:35,416
[RAGNA] Wait,
she's a bounty hunter?

118
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:37,625
They're even giving
out posters of Rawrgna!

119
00:09:37,708 --> 00:09:38,708
[TAOKAKA] Look!

120
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:40,125
[RAGNA] That's not
what I look like!

121
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:41,875
[TAOKAKA] If you see that
face, tell Tao right away!

122
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:45,416
You're a good guy, Good Guy,
so Tao will buy you om noms

123
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,791
with the reward meow-ney!

124
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:48,500
Cross my heart!

125
00:09:48,583 --> 00:09:50,125
[RAGNA] Even if
I tell her my name,

126
00:09:50,208 --> 00:09:53,250
I don't think she's gonna
put two and two together.

127
00:09:53,916 --> 00:09:55,458
[TAOKAKA] No more...

128
00:09:55,541 --> 00:09:57,125
Tao surrenders!

129
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:59,166
Now that the belly is full,

130
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:02,083
it's time to
catnap for a while!

131
00:10:02,166 --> 00:10:03,250
Sleepy, huh?

132
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,333
You're meow-bsolutely
right, Good Guy!

133
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:07,291
Tao's gonna flop
down in a patch of sun

134
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:10,250
[TAOKAKA] and
catch some Zs! Meow!

135
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:25,250
Hey, what's
the matter?

136
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,208
[RAGNA] It's nothing.

137
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:27,500
Huh?

138
00:10:27,583 --> 00:10:28,875
But there's still a bunch
of food in the bowl!

139
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:32,541
Tao calls dibs!
It's all me-ine!

140
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:40,833
[RAGNA panting]

141
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:43,833
Master... Check it out.

142
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:45,875
[JUBEI] Listen up, kid.

143
00:10:45,958 --> 00:10:49,375
The power of the Azure
don't belong to nobody.

144
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:52,375
Don't forget. Ever.

145
00:10:55,541 --> 00:10:58,500
I won't forget. Master.

146
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:05,291
[RACHEL] Your eyes
are filled with hatred.

147
00:11:05,375 --> 00:11:08,208
With loved ones slain
and kin stolen away,

148
00:11:08,291 --> 00:11:11,208
I daresay such
malice is your right.

149
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:14,166
But the world will turn,
as always it has.

150
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:17,166
No matter how you
may rail against it.

151
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:29,708
[footsteps]

152
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:35,291
So this is it. The 13th
Hierarchical City. Kagutsuchi.

153
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:39,541
[HAZAMA] Somebody looks
ready to buy some souvenirs.

154
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:43,000
"Noel Vermillion," wasn't it?

155
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:47,750
Sorry, Captain Hazama!
Please forgive me!

156
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:52,250
[HAZAMA] I suppose I could.
If you stop calling me Captain.

157
00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:55,875
I come from the Intelligence
Department, after all.

158
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:56,958
We're casual.

159
00:11:57,041 --> 00:12:00,125
Yes sir! Uh... I mean...

160
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:04,333
Just call me...
Mister Hazama.

161
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:08,083
[HAZAMA] All right, then!
Let's review the basics.

162
00:12:08,166 --> 00:12:10,250
This whole mess
with Major Kisaragi

163
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:11,333
is being handled with the

164
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:13,458
highest level of
discretion, of course.

165
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:15,416
I mean, if folks
find out that the

166
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,875
Hero of Ikaruga
has gone rogue,

167
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:19,583
the N.O.L.'s gonna
take one on the chin

168
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:21,916
[HAZAMA] in the court
of public opinion.

169
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,458
[HAZAMA] So, if you
encounter the Major,

170
00:12:25,541 --> 00:12:27,125
bag him and bring
him into headquarters

171
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:28,541
with a minimum of fuss.

172
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:29,875
Right!

173
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:31,208
Most secretaries
would give

174
00:12:31,291 --> 00:12:33,583
their eye teeth to
beat up their boss.

175
00:12:36,458 --> 00:12:38,583
Do bear in mind,
a Level D alert is

176
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:42,208
currently in effect here in
the fair city of Kagutsuchi.

177
00:12:42,291 --> 00:12:43,625
It's because
Ragna the Bloodedge

178
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:46,291
has been spotted here
in town, right, sir?

179
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:49,458
He's been hitting N.O.L.
branches, one by one.

180
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:52,333
Right. Have your superiors
told you anything

181
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:54,083
about this Ragna chap?

182
00:12:54,166 --> 00:12:57,083
Oh, uh... They said
to observe him only,

183
00:12:57,166 --> 00:13:00,125
and not to make contact. Sir.

184
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:02,125
[HAZAMA]
Roger that, Lieutenant.

185
00:13:02,958 --> 00:13:04,541
Why don't you go
check out the city,

186
00:13:04,625 --> 00:13:06,791
since we got here so
far ahead of schedule.

187
00:13:06,875 --> 00:13:09,333
We'll meet at the
Kagutsuchi Branch later on.

188
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,833
Sir! I'll get
on that right away!

189
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:16,416
[elevator doors close]

190
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,083
[sighs heavily]

191
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:29,750
You disobedient little minx.

192
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:32,416
[TAOKAKA] ♪ Meow, meow, meow.
Meow, meow, meow ♪

193
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,875
[singing continues]

194
00:13:34,958 --> 00:13:36,375
[grunts]

195
00:13:36,458 --> 00:13:37,375
--[RAGNA] Hey!
--[TAOKAKA] Huh?

196
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:38,875
Why the hell are
you followin' me?

197
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:40,958
[TAOKAKA] Tao's not
following you, Good Guy.

198
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:44,291
You just picked the
direction Te-aow wanted to go!

199
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:45,833
[grunts]

200
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:47,583
[TAOKAKA] Meow!

201
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:48,458
Huh?

202
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:49,625
Ooh...

203
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:51,708
You're playing
keep-away with Tao, huh?!

204
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,375
Whatcha got there, Good Guy?

205
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:55,166
Is it tasty food?

206
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,208
[RAGNA] Hey! Quit it!

207
00:13:57,666 --> 00:13:58,583
[TAOKAKA] Meow!

208
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:02,041
Dammit! Let go
of my arm already!

209
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:05,541
[TAOKAKA] Whoa...
Tao's feelin' kinda mewsy!

210
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:07,416
You're getting on my
nerves, ya damn mooch!

211
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,041
--[TAOKAKA] Meow?
--[RAGNA] Lay off already!

212
00:14:12,625 --> 00:14:15,083
Good Guy got grumpy
all of a sudden.

213
00:14:15,166 --> 00:14:16,916
He should've eaten his food.

214
00:14:21,291 --> 00:14:24,291
Maybe here I can get some
friggin' peace and quiet.

215
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:27,750
[exhales heavily]

216
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,541
Your self-control is laudable.

217
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:36,125
The power of the Azure
don't belong to nobody.

218
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:40,666
Yeah. You're a real
pain in the ass.

219
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:42,208
Aintcha?

220
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:48,125
[exhales]

221
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:15,041
[NOEL] Huh?

222
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:23,583
Saya, come here! Hey!

223
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:32,083
♪

224
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:36,916
[squelch]

225
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,750
[YOUNG RAGNA yells]

226
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:41,625
[RAGNA yells]

227
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:49,666
[RAGNA] Saya?

228
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:50,791
Huh?

229
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:52,166
What the--?

230
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:53,666
Who the hell are you?

231
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:55,291
[NOEL] What? Hold on!

232
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:57,416
You were having
a nightmare.

233
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,541
[NOEL] It must
have been horrible.

234
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,041
Let's see.

235
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:04,583
You're warm, but
you're not feverish.

236
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:06,375
[NOEL] Still,
you might want to have

237
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:08,958
an actual doctor
check you out.

238
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:11,166
[gasps]

239
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:13,083
Something's the
matter with your arm!

240
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:16,041
[RAGNA] Get offa me!

241
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,458
Wait, I--!

242
00:16:21,541 --> 00:16:25,583
Aww. There he goes,
running off like always.

243
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:32,291
"Like always"?

244
00:16:33,375 --> 00:16:35,625
We've never met before.

245
00:16:37,375 --> 00:16:40,166
[footsteps]

246
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:44,375
[RAGNA] The hell's
wrong with this place?

247
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:45,958
I haven't seen anybody.

248
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:47,375
Did the N.O.L. clear
out when they heard

249
00:16:47,458 --> 00:16:50,583
I was coming?
Or maybe it's...

250
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:53,708
A trap.

251
00:16:53,791 --> 00:16:55,833
[MAN] Took you long enough.

252
00:16:55,916 --> 00:16:59,375
[footsteps]

253
00:16:59,458 --> 00:17:01,250
[MAN] We finally meet.

254
00:17:05,541 --> 00:17:07,041
Brother.

255
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:10,125
Jin.

256
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:14,208
[JIN] I'm amazed
you didn't bleed out.

257
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:16,333
And that new arm,
it looks like an

258
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:19,375
improvement over the
one I took from you.

259
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:22,250
This one might not
come off so easily.

260
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:26,625
You bastard!

261
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:28,416
Why?

262
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:32,000
Yes, that strength!
You really are my brother!

263
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:33,333
I've got a bunch
of questions, Jin,

264
00:17:33,416 --> 00:17:35,166
and you're gonna
answer 'em all!

265
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,041
But before that...!

266
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:40,375
I'm gonna beat
the shit outta you!

267
00:17:40,458 --> 00:17:42,791
Let's kill each
other, Brother!

268
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:59,125
Augh!

269
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,541
[JIN chuckles]

270
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:09,666
Goodness! That was
really something!

271
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:13,041
So that's the power of the
Azure Grimoire you wield.

272
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:14,708
I'm glad you're
still alive.

273
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:17,833
I'm having too much fun
for it to be over yet!

274
00:18:19,083 --> 00:18:21,958
Don't tell me you're
getting tired, Brother!

275
00:18:24,875 --> 00:18:26,625
[RAGNA] I've had enough!

276
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:28,958
Huh?

277
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:35,416
[yells]

278
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:48,333
[JIN groans]

279
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:55,333
[JIN] What's the
matter, Brother?

280
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:58,125
Don't have the guts
to finish me off?

281
00:18:58,208 --> 00:19:01,125
Look, dumbass, I didn't come
here today to end your life.

282
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:03,458
If you wanna die,
do it yourself.

283
00:19:04,208 --> 00:19:08,083
Brother, even now
you're merciful.

284
00:19:08,166 --> 00:19:09,750
[chuckles]

285
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,875
That's why you
can't protect anyone.

286
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:14,875
Because you're soft.

287
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:18,083
[chains clanking]

288
00:19:20,541 --> 00:19:23,416
It looks so...
empty.

289
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,125
Maybe Ragna
the Bloodedge

290
00:19:25,208 --> 00:19:26,875
dropped in for
a little bit.

291
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,375
Huh? Hm.

292
00:19:33,791 --> 00:19:34,708
[NOEL gasps]

293
00:19:34,791 --> 00:19:37,333
Major Kisaragi!

294
00:19:37,416 --> 00:19:39,750
He's out cold.
Pardon the pun.

295
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,208
[chuckles]

296
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:45,291
Taking him back with us just
got a whole lot easier, huh?

297
00:19:45,375 --> 00:19:47,500
[HAZAMA] Mission
accomplished, I guess.

298
00:19:47,583 --> 00:19:49,500
Well let's be off!

299
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:50,875
Please, wait!

300
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:53,708
[NOEL] I--I'm gonna pursue
Ragna the Bloodedge!

301
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:55,166
Oh?

302
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:57,458
I thought that the brass
told you not to engage him.

303
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:59,250
[NOEL] It's true, sir.

304
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,708
They did, but given
what happened,

305
00:20:01,791 --> 00:20:03,583
we can't just let him go!

306
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:07,666
[HAZAMA] Well... if it
means that much to you.

307
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:10,875
[NOEL] Mr. Hazama, please
take care of the Major!

308
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:13,291
[NOEL] It looked like
Ragna the Bloodedge

309
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:16,166
almost killed Major
Kisaragi back there.

310
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,875
Why was Captain Hazama
so calm about it?

311
00:20:20,958 --> 00:20:23,083
Uh! Huh?

312
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:42,375
[blast]

313
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:43,833
What the hell?

314
00:20:45,458 --> 00:20:49,250
[RAGNA] Wait! The
Azure Grimoire is afraid?

315
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:56,583
[MAN] It has
been a long time...

316
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:58,041
Dark One.

317
00:20:58,875 --> 00:21:01,916
[RACHEL] You are right
in fearing him, Ragna.

318
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,916
Fear in the face
of absolute power.

319
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,458
Fear of your death.

320
00:21:07,541 --> 00:21:09,916
In all of your duels,

321
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,375
[RACHEL] not once have
you emerged the victor.

322
00:21:13,458 --> 00:21:15,166
Nice mask!

323
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:17,333
Who's under it?

324
00:21:17,416 --> 00:21:19,791
[MAN] I am the white void.

325
00:21:19,875 --> 00:21:21,083
Damn it!

326
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:25,541
[MAN] I am the cold steel.
I am the just sword.

327
00:21:25,625 --> 00:21:26,541
With blade in hand,

328
00:21:26,625 --> 00:21:28,875
shall I reap the
sins of this world

329
00:21:28,958 --> 00:21:31,958
and cleanse it in the
fires of destruction!

330
00:21:33,416 --> 00:21:37,000
[MAN] I am Hakumen!
The end has come!

331
00:23:07,708 --> 00:23:09,208
[RAGNA] O Azure
Grimoire dwelling

332
00:23:09,291 --> 00:23:11,458
within my right arm,
cancel the jinx

333
00:23:11,541 --> 00:23:14,041
on fighting game
anime shows, would ya?

334
00:23:14,125 --> 00:23:17,000
[RACHEL] Episode Two,
"The Azure Successor."

